Suing: Former U.S state Senator Michael Katz and his two daughters were injured when a chairlift derailed and they fell 35ft to the ground

A former U.S state Senator is to sue a ski resort after he and his two daughters were injured when a chairlift derailed sending them falling 35ft to the ground.

Former Democratic politician Michael Katz broke his back and suffered a brain injury in the fall at the Sugarloaf Mountain ski resort in Maine in December 2010.

He was one of eight people injured when high winds dislodged a chairlift cable and five cars were sent plummeting to the ground.

He is the only one of those injured to sue according to, as others have settled out of court.

Mr Katz, who is a doctor, is said to have suffered the worst injuries out of those hurt in the incident.

According to the Portland Press Herald,
Mr Katz is seeking unspecified damages and is also suing on behalf of 
his two daughters who were aged 11 and 13 at the time and were also 
hurt.

