'Abigail and Emily could see their father lying motionless in the snow after the collapse, and their immediate thought was that he had been killed.'

The family say that the resort wa negligent for operating the ski lift even though they were allegedly aware of its safety hazards.

The resort says that it had tried to avoid a court case but that bosses were unsurprised by the legal action.

The lift was an A 2 passenger monocable fixed grip chair manufactured and installed by Borvig in 1975.

It was 4,013 feet long with a vertical of 1,454 feet and moved at a speed of 500 feet per minute.

There were 162 chairs on the lift.

It was removed from the resort shortly after the incident and replaced in December 2011.

Mr Katz only served one term as a Senator before he was defeated at the polls by Republican Greg Lavelle.

